<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 58 Ill by Poisoned Meat in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Two people died and 58
others fell ill in Adaba Area, Bale District in southern Ethiopia
after eating poisoned meat, the Ethiopia News Agency reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
A farmer slaughtered his ox which suddenly fell sick after
grazing on a field sprayed with pesticide, and distributed the
meat among the villagers, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Of the sixty people who ate the meat, two died instantly while
the remaining 58 are under medical care at the Adaba Health
Station, some 300 kms south of the capital Addis Ababa, the
report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
