<HEADLINE> Three Major Opposition Parties Reject Chernomyrdin's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Communist Party
faction will not sign the draft political agreement and will vote
against the candidature of Viktor Chernomyrdin to the post of
prime minister, leader of the communist party Gennady Zyuganov
stated on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov's remarks came Sunday evening after a conference of
the executive and legislative authorities at the State Duma and an
emergency meeting of the Communist Party Central Committee's
presidium in the NTV Itogy television program.
</P>
<P>
In the Itogy television program leader of the Liberal
Democratic faction Vladimir Zhirinovsky said his faction will not
give a single vote to Chernomyrdin as a candidate to the Russian
premier.
</P>
<P>
According to him, a group of governors will appeal to the
Russian president on Monday morning for submitting to the State
Duma a list of three candidates to the premier's post.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, leader of the Yabloko faction Grigory Yavlinsky
announced that he is ready to become the prime minister of Russia
and overcome the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin fired Sergei Kiriyenko's
government entirely on August 23 and named Chernomyrdin as acting
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The tripartite commission Sunday passed a political accord of
compromise and submitted to the president for signature, which
pave the way for the Duma to confirm the president's nomination.
But the situation now is not optimistic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
