<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli army Sunday lifted a 10-day curfew
imposed on the Israeli-controlled areas in the West Bank town of
Hebron, enabling 20,000 Palestinians with work permits in Israel
to return to their works, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
There have been sporadic clashes between Israeli soldiers and
Palestinians since the Israeli army imposed the curfew on the
night of August 20 after a Jewish rabbi was stabbed to death in
his home. (BC-Israel-Hebron-Curfew Lifted)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
