connection with vandalism, attacks against Palestinians in the
West Bank town of Hebron or incitement during demonstrations
outside the residence of Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai, the
radio said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, security has been tightened for Israeli President
Ezer Weizman, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, and Mordechai
amid reports that Jewish extremists are planning to attack or even
assassinate them to head off a possible agreement with the
Palestinians on Israel's overdue withdrawal from the West Bank.
(BC-Israel-Extremists-Detention) 
