<HEADLINE> 3 Mig Fighters Collide in East India, Killing 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A Mig fighter belonging to the
Indian Air Force crash-landed and collided Monday with two
stationary Mig aircraft at an air base in India's eastern state of
West Bengal, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The mishap, which killed three people including a flight
lieutenant, occurred around noon time at the Kalaikunda Air Base
in Midnapore district of the state, said PTI.
</P>
<P>
Flames engulfed all three aircraft and completely gutted them,
PTI said, quoting a local law and order official.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 30 people were killed and 19 injured Monday when a
bus in which they were traveling was hit by a passenger train at
an unmanned crossing in the western state of Rajasthan, according
to PTI.
</P>
<P>
Police in the area said the bus with 49 people on board
suddenly stopped on the rail track while passing the crossing
where the passenger train was approaching.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen people died at the scene and 11 succumbed to their
injuries at a local government hospital, PTI said. 
</P>
