<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women's Movement Must Follow Deng Xiaoping Theory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The women's movement in China
must adhere to the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory to
achieve final success, according to the All-China Women's
Federation (ACWF) which defines its task as seeking true equality
between men and women.
</P>
<P>
"We owe all the achievements for women's movement in China over
the past two decades to the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and
the future of the movement depends on our adherence to that
theory," according to ACWF Vice-President Gu Xiulian. Gu made the
remarks today to the 1,300 delegates attending this afternoon's
opening ceremony of the Eighth National Congress on Chinese Women.
</P>
<P>
"This is an iron-clad conclusion we have drawn from the history
and reality of the women's movement in China," said Gu.
</P>
<P>
She said Deng Xiaoping Theory reflects the Marxist view of the
important role women play in human society, and defines the
correct path to ensure the advancement of the women's movement in
China.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping Theory stresses that ensuring equality between
men and women is a fundamental state policy directly related to
social progress in China, and also provides a theoretical basis
for solving major problems concerning self-improvement for women
under the conditions of the socialist market economy," according
to Gu.
</P>
<P>
She said that studying Deng Xiaoping Theory will enable Chinese
women to get a better understanding of the fact that the
emancipation of women involves a long historical course. She also
stressed that arduous task remains to achieve the true gender
equality as required by law.
</P>
<P>
Gu went on to say that the ACWF has decided to launch a
nationwide campaign to inspire Chinese women to enthusiastically
study Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
She told delegates that the ACWF has set a general goal for the
development of women's movement in China between now and the year
2010.
</P>
<P>
The goal centers on ensuring that the fundamental state policy
of equality between men and women is further implemented
nationwide, and ensuring strengthened protection and improved
conditions for women and children.
</P>
<P>
Chinese women should enjoy greater equality in terms of
economic, political and cultural rights by the year 2010, and
should at the same time see remarkable improvements in their
family life and general quality.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese women must make every effort to abandon the psychology
of inferiority and reliance on men, and constantly create new
female images in line with contemporary trends, while at the same
time carrying forward traditional virtues," said Gu.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
