<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Addresses Legal Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Buhe, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), today
called on NPC deputies and Standing Committee members to fully
understand the Constitution and laws, and to enhance their
awareness of the rule by law.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that an expanded understanding and acute awareness
of related areas is a prerequisite for ensuring their ability to
perform duties outlined by the Constitution and laws.
</P>
<P>
Buhe made the remarks during today's lecture on Agricultural
Law Enforcement and Inspection sponsored by the NPC Standing
Committee. Wu Fuzhao, former deputy director of the NPC Standing
Committee's Commission of Legislative Affairs, and Chen Zongyuan,
vice president of the Chinese Association for the Promotion of
Agricultural Technology, also explained the Agriculture Law and
the Law on Promoting Agricultural Technology, as well as the
status of implementation for same.
</P>
<P>
Buhe pointed out that law enforcement inspection is an
important measure the NPC Standing Committee has introduced to
fulfill its supervision duty. He also pointed to the practical
significance in organizing a lecture on the law prior to the law
enforcement inspection.
</P>
<P>
He said the lecture will provide inspectors with a better
understanding of concerned law, inspection procedures and the
current status of China's agriculture and countryside.
</P>
<P>
Today's lecture was the first the NPC Standing Committee has
sponsored prior to the law enforcement inspection campaign. The
NPC Standing Committee plans to form inspection teams to conduct
inspect implementation of the Agriculture Law in Jiangsu,
Guangdong and Yunnan provinces and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region. 
</P>
