<HEADLINE> Floods Strike Yarlung Zangbo River Valley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- An extended period of heavy rain
has caused severe flooding along the Yarlung Zangbo River in the
Tibet Autonomous Region and inundated vast stretches of land in
the river valley, according to the Ministry of Civil Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Tributaries of the Yarlung Zangbo, including the Lhasa and
Nyang rivers, have recorded several flood crests over the past two
months, with a dramatic rise in water levels along the former,
according to the local meteorological department.
</P>
<P>
The water flow rate in the middle reaches of the Yarlung Zangbo
River stands at 8,500 cu.m./second, with the rate in the lower
reaches of the river reaching 12,800 cu.m./second.
</P>
<P>
Cities and prefectures along the river, including Lhasa,
Xigaze, Loka and Nyingchi, have suffered heavy losses.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary statistics say that flood waters have inundated
14,000 hectares of cropland, killed over 4,000 heads of livestock,
destroyed over 2,000 houses and seriously damaged a large number
of highways and bridges.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from the regional Party Committee, government
and civil affairs departments are directing rescue efforts in
flood-stricken areas. They have also allocated funds totalling six
million yuan (720,000 U.S. dollars) and have supplied over one
million sandbags and 100 tons of wires for the flood control.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
