<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian State Duma Rejects Chernomyrdin's Nomination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma Monday
failed to approve Viktor Chernomyrdin's nomination as prime
minister on the first round of vote.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session of the State Duma, or lower house of
parliament, Chernomyrdin has won only 94 votes for the
presidential motion while 251 deputies voted against him.
</P>
<P>
The nominee needs 226 votes in the 450-seat State Duma to win
approval.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of Russia, which dominates the Duma, and
some other opposition parties had expressed their determination to
vote against Chernomyrdin's candidacy during the parliamentary
session.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Kotenkov, presidential representative to the Duma,
also predicted, "the State Duma will most probably turn down
Viktor Chernomyrdin's candidacy today," the report added.
</P>
<P>
Last week, leaders of the opposition parties and the government
drafted an agreement that would give parliament more power over
the line-up of the cabinet.
</P>
<P>
But President Boris Yeltsin refused to sign the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Before Monday's voting, Chernomyrdin made a 15-minute speech in
the Duma, urging deputies to confirm him in office.
</P>
<P>
He said: " we can no longer let this process continue. We
cannot leave Russia without a government in this situation."
</P>
<P>
"Today's priorities are people's deposits, the ruble rate,
payment of pensions, and wages ... and industrial enterprises," he
added. 
