<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets President of Turkmenistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
met today with Turkmen President S.A. Niyazov and stressed the two
nations should expand cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li extended welcome to Niyazov on behalf of the Chinese
government and Premier Zhu Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Niyazov reached
a wide-ranging consensus during today's highly successful talks,
and said cooperative documents signed by the two nations will
further strengthen friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
He said China and Turkmenistan are close neighbors with highly
complementary economies and great potential for economic and trade
cooperation, Li stressed that the two countries should encourage
strengthened cooperation between enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned, however, that the two sides should pay close
attention to the selection of projects and give full consideration
to the market in order to gradually expand bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li went on to say that the two sides have witnessed smooth
cooperation in the exportation of petroleum machinery and in
restoring oil wells. He also pointed out that China is increasing
exports to Turkmenistan and is considering the establishment of
joint ventures in the country.
</P>
<P>
He said China has a strong capacity and advanced technology in
the production of daily use items and can provide Turkmenistan
with finished products or technology and production lines.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that enterprises from the two nations will
engage in negotiations and strengthen contacts in order to learn
more about cooperative spheres and market demand in order to
promote the development of bilateral economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov pointed to his fruitful talks with President Jiang
Zemin and expressed his belief that the current visit will
accelerate mutually beneficial cooperation in various areas,
including the political and economic and trade arenas. He said
that cooperation will solidify the foundation for the development
of bilateral friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed appreciation of Niyazov's invitation to visit
Turkmenistan. 
</P>
