<HEADLINE> HK Telecom Launches Asia's 1st Remote Access Phonecard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom launched
Monday Asia's first remote-access smart phonecard -- The Hello
Smartcard, the company announced.
</P>
<P>
This new phonecard, incorporating the convenience of remote
access mode and the efficiency of Smart Phonecard, is the fourth
generation phonecard the company put out since it started issuing
phonecards in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The birth of Hello Smartcard represents Hongkong Telecom's
latest successful endeavor in bringing the advantages of advanced
technology into everyday life.
</P>
<P>
With the Hello Smartcard, customers can now easily make local
calls and international calls to cover 230 destinations from any
dial tone phones or payphones in Hong Kong. The cards also can be
used to make calls from over 30 overseas spots back to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
By using the Hello Smartcards, customers can easily obtain the
most up-to-date financial information such as the Hang Seng Index.
</P>
<P>
Hongkong Telecom, a cable and wireless company, is Hong Kong's
only full-service communications provider. 
</P>
</TEXT>
