<HEADLINE> School Cautioned Against Possible Epidemics Outbreaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Health issued an
urgent circular today, urging medical departments at all levels to make
efforts to prevent possible outbreaks of epidemics at school in flood
ravaged areas.
</P>
<P>
The circular said as new school term starts, students are
returning to campus. Schools in flood-stricken areas are striving
to start new school terms in time.
</P>
<P>
However, many school buildings in disastrous areas are
seriously polluted, their sanitation facilities are severely
damaged. Therefore there is potential danger of outbreaks of
epidemic diseases, the circular cautioned.
</P>
<P>
It called on epidemic prevention organizations to step up
guidance and supervision over campus sanitation to ensure teachers
and students have clean food, drinking water and environment.
</P>
<P>
School rooms should be thoroughly disinfected and newly-built
school rooms should meet state sanitation requirements. Lectures
should be given in schools to increase students' health awareness,
said the circular.
</P>
<P>
Students should have health check, especially those from
flood-hit regions, to prevent contagious diseases from spreading
on campus.
</P>
<P>
Medical departments should have adequate stocks of medicines
for fighting against possible epidemics, the circular
noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
