<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Leaves For Durban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga Monday left here for Durban, South Africa to attend
the summit of the Non-Aligned Movement (NAM), according official
radio Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The two-day summit of NAM will begin on Wednesday. Chandrika
Kumaratunga is due to make a speech at the inauguration of the NAM
summit.
