<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets President of Turkmenistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, China's top legislator,
met today with S.A. Niyazov, President of Turkmenistan, and noted
that the two nations have continually strengthened political ties,
and witnessed constantly expanding economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Scientific, technological and cultural exchanges have grown
steadily, said Li, chairman of the National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li praised Niyazov's positive contributions to related efforts,
and expressed great pleasure at once again having the opportunity
to meet the president. He noted their last meeting took place some
four years ago during his tenure as premier.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that Niyazov's current visit will serve
to strengthen friendly cooperative ties and consolidate the
people-to-people friendship.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov is on a six-day state visit as guest of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin. China and Turkmenistan established
diplomatic ties six years ago.
</P>
<P>
China treasures and strives to further develop friendly
cooperative relations with Turkmenistan in various areas, said Li,
adding that "this is the set policy we will adhere to in the
future."
</P>
<P>
Li responded to Niyazov's briefing on the domestic situation in
Turkmenistan by noting that the president's leadership has been a
catalyst promoting political stability, economic recovery and
expanding diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
"We appreciate the notable achievements," said Li, adding the
facts prove the correctness of Turkmenistan's economic and social
policies based on stable conditions.
</P>
<P>
Li said extensive friendly contacts the NPC has established
with the Turkmenistan's Grand National Assembly since the
establishment of diplomatic ties have served as important channel
enabling the two nations to strengthen mutual understanding and
friendship.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully prepared to expand legislative contacts and join
in a concerted effort to promote the comprehensive development of
exchanges and cooperation in various sectors between the two
countries," said Li.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov invited Li to visit Turkmenistan and noted his great
satisfaction with the positive results of today's talks with
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Turkmenistan will strictly adhere to the "one
China" policy, and expressed his firm conviction that mutually
beneficial cooperation will witness steady advancement in the 21st
century. 
</P>
