<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Meet to Discuss Women and Children Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,300 women delegates
from all over China met here this afternoon to discuss issues
related to women and children.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and senior leaders Li Peng, Li
Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing, along with the
delegates, attended the opening session of the Eighth National
Congress of Chinese Women, which opened this afternoon in the
Great Hall of the People in downtown Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, president of the All-China Women's Federation,
presided over the session.
</P>
<P>
Representing the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC), Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao delivered a
congratulatory speech to the session.
</P>
<P>
Women constitute half of the Chinese's population and they are
playing an indispensable role in pushing forward the grand cause
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
China has entered into a crucial stage in its reform drive, and
women's active participation and creativity are needed to further
promote the cause, he said, adding that women should support and
adhere to the reform measures adopted by the the Party and
government, striving to maintain political stability.
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed out that women should study hard to further their
knowledge and competitiveness, which will not only be helpful for
their career development but will also improve the general
cultural level of the entire country.
</P>
<P>
Paying respect and offering protection to women are indicators
of a society's progress, he said, emphasizing that the Chinese
government has always regarded equality between men and women as a
fundamental state policy for promoting China's social development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will severely punish criminal activities
affecting women and children, and make the uttermost efforts to
eliminate social evils and create favorable conditions for
promoting excellent women cadres, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,300 women delegates from around the country,
including the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macao and
Taiwan, are attending the conference, which is the highest organ
of the All-China Women's Federation, and convenes once every five
years.
</P>
<P>
Gu Xiulian, executive chairwoman of the Presidium of the
conference, made a work report at today's session on behalf of the
Seventh Executive Committee of the All-China Women's Federation.
</P>
<P>
She described the past five years as one of the best periods
for the development of women's movement in China since 1949, and
promised that the Federation would make greater efforts to enhance
women's role in the Chinese society and protect all women's and
children's legitimate rights and interests.
</P>
<P>
The conference, which is expected to last six days till
September 5, will elect a new term of leadership for the All-China
Women's Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
