<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Export Earnings Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's export earnings
showed a 9.3 percent rise during the first half of this year over
the same period last year, according to latest Central Bank
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Bank sources said Monday the increased foreign exchange income
from January to June this year of 2.115 billion U.S. dollars was
mainly due to enhanced exports of agricultural and industrial
products.
</P>
<P>
The value of industrial exports rose to 1.546 billion dollars
from 1.334 billion dollars while 527 million dollars worth of
agricultural produce was exported, when compared to an earning of
415 million dollars the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the industrial sector, the top position went to the textiles
and apparel exports, followed by leather and rubber products, said
the sources, adding that however, the country's mineral exports
declined in the first six months. 
