<HEADLINE> Listed Companies Report Declining Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Companies listed on the Shenzhen
Stock Exchange fell during the first half of 1998 due at least in
part to the Asia Financial Crisis, according to interim reports
released today.
</P>
<P>
The reports indicate that the per share earnings of 391 listed
companies ended the period at 0.1154 yuan, down 26 percent over on
the same period last year. However, 118 companies enjoyed rising
momentum, with average growth standing at nine percent.
</P>
<P>
The net assets return rate averaged 3.77 percent, down 39
percent, with only 97 companies reporting growth.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that that per share earnings for 50 listed
high-tech listed companies hit 0.19 yuan, some 60 percent higher
than the average level, with their net assets return rate
averaging 6.37 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts note the performance of listed companies is
expected to improve as the country introduces additional measures
to improve the macroeconomic environment in the second half of the
year.  
