<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Enjoy Better Social Status (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The past five years has
witnessed of the best periods in history in terms of improvements
in the social status of Chinese women, according to a senior
official with the All-China Women's Federation (ACWF).
</P>
<P>
Women have made great contribution to China's economic
development in recent years, according to ACWF Vice-President Gu
Xiulian. Gu made the remarks today at the opening ceremony of the
Eighth National Congress of Chinese Women.
</P>
<P>
Gu said women account for more than 60 percent of the total
number of rural laborers and 40 percent of the work force for
township enterprises. She said women also play an important role
in economic development and scientific progress in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The role of women in state and government affairs has also
been enhanced, said Gu, adding that 650 women, or 21.8 percent of
the total, were elected deputies to the Ninth National
People's Congress. An additional 341 women, or 15.5 percent of the
total, were elected members of the Ninth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
She added that the total number of female deputies to people's
congresses and CPPCC committees at all levels has increased
considerably during recent elections.
</P>
</TEXT>
