<HEADLINE> Macao People Show Great Care for Flood-Hit Compatriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Over the past days, Macao people
continued various activities to raise more money for the flood-hit
areas in central and northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Up to August 30, the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch had
received more than 26 million patacas (about 3.25 million
U.S. dollars) of donations.
</P>
<P>
On the evening of August 28, the Macao Broadcast and Television
Co. Ltd., the Welfare Association "Tong Sin Tong" and the General
Union of the Macao Neighborhood Associations jointly held an
evening party to raise donations.
</P>
<P>
Along with the colorful artistic performances, people of
various sectors were active and generous in offering money and
expressing their sincerity for their compatriots in the
motherland. By the end of the party, a total of 2.3 million
patacas were raised.
</P>
<P>
The local TV station broadcast the evening party live. In
addition, around-the-clock hotlines and special banking accounts
were opened to facilitate Macao residents to donate.
</P>
<P>
That same day, the Macao Federation of Fish Dealers organized
lion dancing in the streets or fish markets to attract donors.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of artistic societies in Macao have also been sparing no
efforts to hold benefit performances.
</P>
<P>
On August 30, the Macao Federation of Trade Unions organized
grand benefit sale. All the goods including shoes, clothes,
ornaments, toys, daily necessities, paintings and special foods
were donated by more than 30 companies, factories or stores in
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there were games, kalaoke singing and lion dancing
to entertain visitors. Over 172,500 patacas were collected that
day.
</P>
<P>
During their summer holidays, many young students have also
been organized to participate in benefit performances together
with adults or collect donations along the streets. 
</P>
