<HEADLINE> China Telecom Announces Satisfactory Interim Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-listed China Telecom
announced satisfactory interim results on Monday, based on the
rapid growth in the mobile telecommunications businesses on the
Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
For the first six months ended June 30, 1998, the blue-chip
company recorded a net profit of 3.47 billion yuan (419 million
U.S. dollars), while revenue amounting to 11.37 billion yuan (1.4
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shi Cuiming, chairman of the blue-chip company, told a press
conference that he was pleased with the results and fully
confident in the company's future prospects.
</P>
<P>
Following a multi-billion-HK-dollar acquisition of Jiangsu
Mobile earlier this year, China Telecom now owns cellular
telecommunications businesses in Guangdong, Zhejiang and Jiangsu,
all of which are among China's richest and fastest growing
provinces.
</P>
<P>
The company's cellular subscriber number reached 5,452 million
by the end of June, up 27 percent over half a year ago.
</P>
<P>
With the continued economic growth in China, the company faces
strong market demand and enjoys a huge market with enormous growth
potential, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
The company will continue to explore opportunities to acquire
high quality assets on the mainland, he added.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom was listed concurrently in Hong Kong and New York
in October last year and was added to the 33-stock Hang Seng Index
on January 27, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
