<HEADLINE> Singapore Stock Market Closes Sharply Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Haunting fears of a global
equities meltdown pulled down Singapore Stock Market sharply lower
Monday as the newly-introduced benchmark Straits Times Index (STI)
replaced the 30-year old Straits Times Industrial Index (STII) as
the dominant barometer of the stock market.
</P>
<P>
The 55-stock STI, that picked up from where the phased-out
30-counter STII left off to ensure continuity, plunged by 28.83
points to close at 856.43 points. The STI was expected to better
reflect the market trend.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 195.72 million units worth 311.71
million Singapore dollars (about 175.18 million U.S. dollars).
Decliners outnumbered advancers by 213 to 55 with 321 counters
unchanged
</P>
<P>
ST Engg was the most active stock of the day as it surged up on
a turnover of 46.46 million stocks. It was followed by SingTel
that had 15.23 million units traded. IPC was next with 12.45
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Jar Mat and Venture w99 topped the gainers of the day as they
both gained 12 cents and finished at 1.78 U.S. dollars and 3.40
Singapore dollars respectively. SemCorp was up 11 cents to end at
2.14 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 was the biggest loser of the day as it registered a
loss of 90 cents and ended at 17.30 Singapore dollars. Robinson
slid by 60 cents to close at 4.00 Singapore dollars. DPS F was
down 50 cents to finish at 6.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said investors were all so sidelined by concerns over
Russia's political and economic crises.
</P>
<P>
The market sentiment was also depressed by the weaker Hong Kong
market and the expectations that more negative news will creep out
on corporate results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
