<TEXT>
<P>
DURBAN (South Africa), August 31 (Xinhua)-- The foreign
Ministers meeting of the Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) opened here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to the session, South African Deputy President
Thabo Mbeki called on the NAM members to work hard to eliminate
poverty in their countries, to improve the quality of life of the
people, to close up the gap between the rich and the poor and to
attain sustainable rates of economic growth and development.
</P>
