<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 11:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Cypriot Leader Proposes Confederation in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash Monday proposed a confederation composed of the Greek and
Turkish communities in Cyprus to end the 24-year-old division of
the island.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Turkish Cypriot regime reaching here
termed the proposal as "a final effort" to achieve a mutually
acceptable lasting solution in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Denktash made the proposal for the confederation of "two
peoples and two states" at a press conference in Nicosia with the
presense of visiting Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem.
</P>
<P>
The condition Denktash set to the negotiations for the
confederation is the acknowledgement of the Turkish Cypriot side
as a "sovereign and equal" state as the Greek Cypriot side.
</P>
<P>
Denktash also proposed a special "symmetrical ties" between
Turkey and the Turkish Cypriots and between Greece and the Greek
Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974 when Turkey landed its
troops and took over the northern third after a failed coup by the
Greek Cypriots seeking union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriots declared in 1983 the breakaway "Turkish
Republic of Northern Cyprus" recognized only by Ankara, against
the internationally acknowledged Republic of Cyprus dominated by
the Greek Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cem said his presence at the press conference is an expression
of "the Turkish Government's support and trust for President
Denktash."
</P>
<P>
Denktash said the 1960 guarantee system adopted at the founding
of the Republic of Cyprus should continue should the Cyprus
Confederation be established.
</P>
<P>
Britain, Greece and Turkey are the three guarantors of Cyprus'
independence from an 82-year-old British colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Confederation may, if both parties jointly agree,
pursue a policy of accession to the European Union (EU), said
Denktash.
</P>
<P>
Until Turkey's full membership to the EU, a special arrangement
will provide Turkey with the full rights and obligations of an EU
member with regard to the Cyprus Confederation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is maintaining more than 35,000 troops with a claimed
aim to protect Turkish Cypriots in northern Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
The peace negotiations between the Greek and Turkish
communities broke down last summer after Denktash walked out to
protest EU's decision to start accession talks with the Cypriot
government, rather than the Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriot leader pointed out that "if the Greek
Cypriots agree to this final basis, we are ready to begin
negotiations to establish the Cyprus Confederation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980831.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 69.12 PCT Inflation in 8 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia posted a 69.12 percent
inflation in the first eight months this year, the Central
Statistics Agency announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in August was 6.3 percent, much higher than
the corresponding period of last year which stood at 0.88 percent,
said the agency's chief Sugito Suwito.
</P>
<P>
Sugito said the main cause of the higher inflation was a 2.45
percent increase in foods price.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the inflation rate for the whole year would
reach as high as 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation rate was 11.05 percent Last year.
</P>
