"It seems like they haven't got their eye on it (the Australian
dollar) too much," he said.
</P>
<P>
Traders said speculation of a hike in official interest rates
continued to circulate in the market but most players rated any
move unlikely.
</P>
<P>
The recent fall in the Australian dollar had prompted fears of
imported inflation and spurred talk of a rate rise by the Reserve
Bank of Australia.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed trading in Sydney at 80.35
Japanese yen from 80.27 yen and 0.9998 German marks from 1.0058
marks. 
