<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Turkmen Presidents Hold Talks in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- During talks with Turkmen
President S. A. Niyazov here this morning, Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said the Chinese government values very much its friendship and
cooperation with Turkmenistan, which accords with the fundamental
interests of the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral ties in various fields have witnessed
smooth development with increased mutual trust since the two
forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for the position of the Turkmen
government in supporting China on issues of Taiwan and of opposing
national splittism.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his appreciation for the Turkmen government's
efforts to maintain domestic stability and develop its economy, as
well as its pursuit of an independent foreign policy of neutrality
and the expansion of international exchange and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China respects the road of development chosen by the Turkmen
people and will, as always, support the country's efforts to
safeguard its independence and sovereignty while maintaining
domestic stability and advancing its economy, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of Sino-Turkmen economic and trade cooperation, Jiang
noted that the scale of cooperation remains relatively small and
there is potential to be tapped in this area.
</P>
<P>
However, China and Turkmenistan enjoy a good political
relationship, and bilateral economic and trade ties will reach a
new level if the two sides make concerted efforts to encourage
business people in the two countries to collaborate on the basis
of equality and mutual benefit, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
