<HEADLINE> Chile Donates 100,000 Yuan to China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- On behalf of the Chinese
government, Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan today accepted a
donation of 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 U.S. dollars) from Chile's
ambassador to China Octario Errazuriz Guilisasti to China's flood
victims.
</P>
<P>
This donation was a part of the expenditures for receptions
marking Chile's National Day by the Chilean embassy in Beijing and
general consulates in Shanghai and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tang quoted the Chinese proverb: "A friend in need is a
friend indeed." He said the donation fully exhibits the friendly
feeling of the Chilean government and its embassy and general
consulates for the Chinese government and people.
</P>
<P>
This gift not only means material assistance, but can be seen
as spiritual support, he said, adding that it will encourage the
flood victims to overcome difficulty and rebuild their homelands.
</P>
<P>
Octario Errazuriz Guilisasti said the Chilean government and
people have expressed deep concern and sympathy for the loss of
life and property in the flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes the Chinese government and people will
certainly win their battle against this disaster. 
</P>
