<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stolen Mural Returned Mysteriously </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Colin McCahon's Urewera Mural
worth more than 1.2 million New Zealand dollars or 600,000 U.S.
dollars, which was stolen from the Aniwaniwa Visitors' Center of
New Zealand Conservation Department on June 5 last year, returned
in mysterious circumstances at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The Evening Post reported Monday that Auckland millionairess
and art collector Jenny Gibbs, who had been working on the return
of the three-part mural, negotiated its return in intriguing
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the painting was in "surprisingly good"
condition. 
