<HEADLINE> World's Second Largest Bronze Statue Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A giant bronze sculpture was
unveiled recently in north China's Shanxi Province. It is believed
to be the second largest in the world next to the Statue of
Liberty in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The 39-meter-tall statue weighs more than 150 tons. About 10
companies have spent eight years on the giant sculpture.
</P>
<P>
According to the designer, Qian Shaowu, it is a statue of Shen
Nong, a legendary ruler of China's remote antiquity who taught
people how to farm and weave.
</P>
<P>
Inside the statue, there are stairs for visitors to go to the
top for a commanding view.  
</P>
