<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0700 GMT, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Five Israeli soldiers were wounded early Monday in an
attack by the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, in south
Lebanon, Lebanon's Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The five were wounded in the explosion of a remote-controlled
bomb planted at the Dabshi village in the central sector of the
Israeli occupied zone in south Lebanon when an Israeli patrol was
passing by. (South Lebanon-Israelis Wounded)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB -- The United States supports the incumbent Bosnian Serb
leaders in Bosnia's September general election and will approve
100 million U.S. dollars in assistance to the Serb entity by the
end of the year, according to reports reaching here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. commitment is based on condition that Bosnian Serbs
should implement the U.S.-brokered Dayton Accord that halted the
1992-95 Bosnian war, Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said
after talks with President of the Republika Srpska Bilijana
Plavsic and Prime Minister Milorad Dodik in Bijeljina. Albright
added she also reminded the Bosnian Serb leaders that the Dayton
agreement could bring jobs and income to the Bosnian Serbs.
(Bosnia-Albright-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia's three major party leaders expressed their
opposition Sunday to the appointment of Viktor Chernomyrdin as
Russian prime minister, casting a shadow again over the solution
to the Russian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Gennady Zyuganov, chairman of the Russian Communist Party, said
Sunday at Russia's Independence TV program that he would persuade
all Communist parliamentary members to vote against Chernomyrdin's
nomination at the State Duma (lower house of the parliament)
meeting Monday. (Russia-Zyuganov)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslavia's news media reported Sunday that 22
kidnapped Serb civilians were killed by Kosovo ethnic Albanian
rebels in the village of Klecka.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav authorities accused the ethnic Albanian rebels of
killing the Serbs and burning their bodies in a crematory in the
village Serb forces recaptured this week, said the reports. The
alleged crematory was found based on testimony from two captured
rebels who told police that at least 22 Serbs were killed in
July. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo-Killing) 
</P>
