ever to visit China, by saying "China and New Zealand share
common interests and responsibilities in safeguarding regional
peace and stability and promoting economic prosperity and
development."
</P>
<P>
Chi added that China is satisfied with the growth of bilateral
relations, in particular the mutual visits paid by the two defence
ministers this year.
</P>
<P>
"We hold a positive attitude for promoting the exchanges
between the two armies," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bradford stressed that New Zealand and China maintain a stable
and sound bilateral relationship and play positive roles in
regional safety and development. He told Chi that his country is
willing to enhance cooperation with China and further advance the
ties between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Chi hosted a welcoming ceremony for
Bradford and his party, who arrived China on Sunday. 
