<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Undertakes Agricultural Credit Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
undertaken a 32.7 billion taka (695.7 million U.S. dollars)
agricultural credit program to strengthen the post-flood
agricultural rehabilitation activities, The New Nation daily
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made Sunday at a meeting chaired by Finance
Minister A.M.S. Kabria.
</P>
<P>
Of the total amount, 15 billion taka (319.15 million dollars)
will be disbursed by banks and other financial institutions as
crop loan, while the rest will be disbursed for fisheries,
livestock, poultry and procurement of other agricultural inputs
and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government has also decided to provide fresh
loans to the flood-affected farmers in the current fiscal year
holding off the repayment of their outstanding loan of the fiscal
1997-98 for one year, the paper quoted sources close to the
meeting as saying.
</P>
<P>
The farmers, who had taken agricultural loan up to 15,000 taka
(319 dollars) in 1997-98 but now are unable to repay due to flood,
will be eligible for the fresh loan.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the farmers who had taken agricultural loan during
July-August of the 1998-99 fiscal year and fell victim to flood
will also be eligible for fresh loan. The loan facilities will
also be applicable to the cooperative farmers.
</P>
<P>
The finance minister stressed the role of rural economic
activities in the national economy and directed the authorities
concerned to gear up the monitoring activities to ensure smooth
disbursement of the loan.
</P>
<P>
The floods, which started in early July, have hit 45 out of the
country's 64 districts, with over 400 people dead and more than
40.2 million people affected in the country.
</P>
<P>
Crops on over 214,000 hectares have been washed away or damaged
by floods, with an estimated crop loss amounting to 14.22 billion
taka (302.6 million dollars), the Ministry of Agriculture said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
