<HEADLINE> Dalian's Foreign-funded Firms Doing Well in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- In spite of the negative impact
of the Asian financial crisis, the exports of this seaport city in
northeast China's Liaoning Province registered continuous growth
in the first seven months of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that the exports of the city reached
1.32 billion U.S. dollars during the period, up nearly 30 percent
on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the achievement to the marketing strategy of
local foreign-funded enterprises which resulted in timely changes
of focus from Southeast Asian countries to Europe and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The growth also is the result of optimizing the export products
structure, insiders said.
</P>
<P>
Aquatic products and clothing used to be Dalian's major
exports, but these have been replaced by electronic products and
machinery.
</P>
<P>
The city currently has 6,500 foreign-funded firms, with a total
investment of 22 billion U.S. dollars. 
