<HEADLINE> More Chinese Renting Potted Plants to Decorate Apartments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Decorating apartments with
potted plants rented from flower shops has become popular among
city dwellers in China, especially those in the prosperous coastal
regions.
</P>
<P>
"Initially, our customers were major enterprises and government
institutions," said Wang Bingjing, manager of a flower shop in
Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, however, more and more ordinary residents
begin to decorate their apartments with rented miniature plants,"
Wang said.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey of the city's residents indicates that more
than 60 percent of the city dwellers expressed their "welcome" of
the rental service.
</P>
<P>
"Each week we send workers to tend to miniature plants at the
customers' apartments and we also pledge the service of exchanging
new kinds of miniature plants for our customers," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Observers here attribute the trend to improved living standards
of the Chinese citizens. 
</P>
