<HEADLINE> Publishing Houses in Anhui Province Expediting Textbooks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The publishing houses in east
China's Anhui Province, which was heavily affected by flooding
this summer, aim to ensure that every primary and secondary
student in the province receives textbooks before the new semester
begins.
</P>
<P>
To date, 180 million textbooks have been distributed across the
province.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing floods have affected 250,000 students in 1,032
provincial schools, and each of the students use an average of 66
yuan worth of textbooks.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government recently issued a notice
encouraging staff members of all publishing houses to work
around-the-clock if necessary to ensure that students have
textbooks before the new semester begins, whether they can pay or
not. 
