<HEADLINE> Ethnic Albanian Rebels Reportedly Kill 22 Civilians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's mass media
reported Sunday that 22 kidnapped Serb civilians were killed by
Kosovo ethnic Albanian rebels in the village of Klecka.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav authorities accused the ethnic Albanian rebels of
killing the Serbs and burning their bodies in a crematory in the
village Serb forces recaptured this week, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The victims include women, children and the old, said the
reports. The alleged crematory was found based on testimony from
two captured rebels who told police that at least 22 Serbs were
killed in July.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav Foreign Ministry issued a statement, appealing to
other countries for support of its fight against terrorism,
Various parties of Yugoslavia condemned the massacre.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanian rebels have kidnapped 171 civilians over
the past seven months, including 125 ethnic Serbians and
Montenegrins as well as 37 ethnic Albanians loyal to the Serbian
authorities, the official Tanjug news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a province of Serbia, the dominant Yugoslav
republic. Ethnic Albanians account for a majority in the
province. Armed Albanian rebels have fought government forces to
seek Kosovo's secession from the Yugoslav republic. 
</P>
