</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk on Sunday urged
Cambodian political leaders to resolve disputes through dialogues,
in an effort to calm the political unrest haunting the country in
recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
In a message delivered from Siemreap, Sihanouk called on those
ready to use violence to avoid such acts, saying that they are
against the Constitution and laws of the country and are
detrimental to the interest of the people.
</P>
<P>
Though the "serious events" happening in recent weeks could not
be termed as violence, the king said, they have drawn serious
criticism from the international community.
</P>
<P>
Sihanouk also voice worries that if friendly countries stopped
providing aid, Cambodians would plunge deeper into poverty and
desperation.
</P>
<P>
Cambodian politicians have to solve their differences through
talks, he said. (Cambodia-Sihanouk-Message) 
