<HEADLINE> King Wins Women's Title at Triathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Joanne King of Australia won the
women's title at the World Triathlon Championships at Lausanne on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
King was the surprise winner at the championships. She
completed the 1.5-kilometer swim, 40-kilometer cycling and
10-kilometer running in a total time of two hours 7 minutes and
25.3 seconds.
</P>
<P>
King's compatriot Michellie Jones finished second and failed
to claim a record third world title.
</P>
<P>
Jones, back-to-back champion in 1992-1993, improved on her
bronze medal from last year's worlds in Perth, Australia,claiming
the silver in 2:08:03.90.
</P>
<P>
Evelyn Williamson of New Zealand completed a South Pacific
sweep of the podium, finishing third in 2:08:12.20.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion and ITU World Cup points leader Emma Carney
of Australia, had a disappointing race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
