<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafter Beats Mantilla to Win Hamlet Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Patrick Rafter
won his final match before beginning defense of his U.S. Open
title, downing eighth seed Felix Mantilla of Spain 7-6 (7-3), 6-2
Sunday in the 315,000 U.S. dollars Hamlet Cup tennis event in New
York, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Rafter improved to 18-2 during the summer
hardcourt season with his fifth title of the year, the most by an
Australian since John Mewcombe won nine and Rod Laver claimed
five in 1974. Last year, he went 0-for-4 in finals before his
triumph at Flushing.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't want to lose going into the U.S. Open," said
Rafter,who played with a wrap on his injured Achilles tendon as a
precaution, "I started to hit the ball well, regardless of the
result. This is the best I've played over such a long period of
time. I'm confident now."
</P>
<P>
Rafter earned 45,000 U.S. dollars with his third victory over
Mantilla in as many meetings. The 25-year-old Australian is
seeded third at the U.S. Open, which begins Monday in New York.
The last player to parlay a win at the Hamlet into a victory at
the final Grand Slam event of the year was Ivan Lendl. Rafter
plays Hicham Arazi of Morocco in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
